<br>
I am one of the enchanters that likes to have a bard in my group.  With a bard and an enchanter in your group, you have little to no downtime.<br>
<br>
Here are some tips on working with a bard that i have found.  Please, others feel free to jump in :<br>
<br>
1) Find out if the bard will be doing damage via song, or melee ( or both with epic ).  I dont necessarily speed bards out of hand, since haste is a lot of mana and if they arent meleeing it is not worth it obviously.  DO haste them if they choose to melee.<br>
<br>
2)Dont request clarity song.<br>
<br>
Nothing seems to piss bards off more than &quot;mana song plz, thx&quot;.  I have found that if you are low mana, and not getting mana song, just mentioning that fact will more often than not get you mana song without having to ask for it.  Saying &quot; 20m &quot; to a competant bard, will get you mana song usually.<br>
<br>
3) be prepared to swollow your pride if it is for the good of the group .<br>
<br>
What i mean by this is, we all know the single most influencing factor of determining if your mez will stick is level.  Yes there are other factors, but level is king in eq as we all say.  If you join a group at level 52, and there is a level 57 bard there, consider giving over the mezz duties to that bard (if they want them).  Bards are very effective in crowd control, and that 57 bard is going to get less resist than you, thereby taking less mana to heal etc etc.  I personally feel that if the group is similarly leveled, the enchanter should do the Crowd Control, but if the group ISNT, be prepared to give up those duties for the good of the group.<br>
<br>
As enchanters, that is one of THE hardest things you will do, but , just pretend that 57 bard is a 57 enchanter ( if your 52 for example ), and support them with color stuns and such as you would an enchanter.  The bard may not always want this duty, but , if they do, its ok to let them do it.<br>
<br>
4) If you are on primary CC duties, ask the bard in tells to back you up if you get into trouble.<br>
<br>
If you are doing the crowd control duties, ask the bard in tells if he or she can back you up.  This lets the bard know that you wont throw a hissy fit if he mezzes something thats beating on you, etc, and lets them know their help is appreciated.<br>
<br>
5) dont be afraid to charm mobs , since you have backup with crowd control duties. <br>
<br>
Some people shy away from charm due to the random nature of the spell breaking.  If there is another class that can help you retake control of the charmed mob ( like a bard can ), there is no reason to resist using this spell more often to take advantage of the awesome damage potential of charmed pets.<br>
<br>
<br>
Those are just some things off the top of my head.  Anyone else feel free to jump in.<br>
